As an evolutionary scale developed to aid historians and [[Xenoarchaeology|xenoarchaeologists]] in classifying a civilization's level of technology, the '''Pantang Scale of Aero-techno Advancement''' was not a popular classification system. The primary reason this was that it rated technology required to build a [[Landspeeder/Legends|landspeeder]] as equivalent to that required to build an [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]].

